thorough /ˈθʌrə/

1. ADJ A thorough action or activity is one that is done very carefully and in a detailed way so that nothing is forgotten. 彻底的 

例： We are making a thorough investigation. 我们正在进行彻底的调查。 

例： This very thorough survey goes back to 

1784. 这项非常彻底的调查可追溯到1784年。 

2. thoroughly ADV 彻底地 [ADV with v] 

例： Food that is being offered hot must be reheated thoroughly. 热熟食拿到手后必须重新热透。 

3. ADJ Someone who is thorough is always very careful in their work, so that nothing is forgotten. 细心的 

例： Martin would be a good judge, I thought. He was calm and thorough. 我想马丁会是个好法官。他既沉着又细心。 

4. thoroughness N-UNCOUNT 细心 

例： His thoroughness and attention to detail is legendary. 他的细心和对细节的关注是很有名的。 

5. ADJ Thorough is used to emphasize the large degree or extent of something. (用于强调程度或范围) 完全的 [det ADJ] [强调] 

例： To me, this seemed like a thorough waste of time. 在我看来，这好像完全是浪费时间。 

6. thoroughly ADV 完全地 

例： I thoroughly enjoy your programme. 我非常喜欢你们的节目。

